      "content": "that's a good point about the systemic stuff. but i also want to be thorough in my review. some researchers argue that even when you control for income and education, there are still certain cultural or behavioral patterns that explain the variance in these stats. how would a researcher who holds that view justify their position, and are there any specific studies that support the idea of cultural or inherent group differences as a factor?",
